<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,498,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
This species is compared by Gravenhorst with 
<taxonomicName box="[661,862,498,521]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalybaeum">
<emphasis box="[661,862,498,521]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Apion chalybaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a name apparently not referable to any species then known.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,498,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
The examination of the original copy of the author’s book, with his handwritten notes, allows for attribution of this name to 
<taxonomicName box="[251,461,602,625]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Curculio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalybeus">
<emphasis box="[251,461,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Curculio chalybeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, [
<bibRefCitation author="Gmelin" box="[486,650,602,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" refString="Gmelin, J. F. (1790) Caroli a Linne systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Editio decimatertia, aucta, reformata. Tom. I. Pars IV. Georg Emanuel Beer, Lipsiae, 708 pp. [pp. 1517 - 2224]" type="book chapter" year="1790">
Gmelin], 
<number box="[594,650,602,625]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1790.0">1790</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, currently placed as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Scopoli, 1763" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1763" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Aulacobaris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coerulescens">
<emphasis box="[1049,1328,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Aulacobaris coerulescens</emphasis>
(Scopoli, 
<number box="[151,208,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1763.0">1763</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, the description of the prothorax of 
<taxonomicName box="[722,878,637,660]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratum">
<emphasis box="[722,878,637,660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Apion atratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gravenhorst" box="[989,1256,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" refString="Gravenhorst, I. L. C. (1807) Vergleichende Uebersicht des Linneischen und einiger neuern zoologischen Systeme, nebst dem eigeschalteten Verzeichnisse der zoologischen Sammlungen des Verfassers und den Beschreibungen neuer Thierarten, die in derselben vorhanden sind. Dieterich, Gottingen, XX + 476 pp." type="book" year="1807">
Gravenhorst (
<number box="[1138,1196,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1807.0">1807</number>
: 
<number box="[1208,1248,637,660]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="198.0">198</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
—“... ohne allen Glanz und durch grobe Punkte rauh ist 
<emphasis box="[571,591,672,695]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">...</emphasis>
”—does not fit our present concept of the baridine weevil described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gmelin" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" refString="Gmelin, J. F. (1790) Caroli a Linne systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Editio decimatertia, aucta, reformata. Tom. I. Pars IV. Georg Emanuel Beer, Lipsiae, 708 pp. [pp. 1517 - 2224]" type="book chapter" year="1790">
Gmelin (
<number box="[159,217,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1790.0">1790</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[228,286,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1759.0">1759</number>
). Despite this and despite the black colour mentioned by Gravenhorst, surely due to grease present on the integument (as sometimes happens), the description of the prothoracic punctation suggests 
<taxonomicName box="[1131,1246,741,764]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratum">
<emphasis box="[1131,1246,741,764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">A. atratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="Marsham, 1802" authorityName="Marsham" authorityYear="1802" box="[206,648,776,799]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Perapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hydrolapathi">
<emphasis box="[206,450,776,799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Perapion hydrolapathi</emphasis>
(Marsham, 
<number box="[582,639,776,799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1802.0">1802</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, I have decided to designate a specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1241,1406,776,799]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Perapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hydrolapathi">
<emphasis box="[1241,1406,776,799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">P. hydrolapathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[194,278,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[322,440,810,833]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratum">
<emphasis box="[322,440,810,833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">A. atratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is a male (fig. 
<number box="[654,666,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1.0">1</number>
) labelled: Neustrelitz Fasanerie, 
<date box="[1036,1118,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="75-07-24">
<number box="[1036,1087,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="24.7">24.7</number>
. 
<number box="[1090,1118,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="75.0">75</number>
</date>
, Stäckel / 
<typeStatus box="[1240,1362,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">NEOTYPE</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Gravenhorst, 1807" authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1807" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Apion atratum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gravenhorst" box="[247,454,845,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" refString="Gravenhorst, I. L. C. (1807) Vergleichende Uebersicht des Linneischen und einiger neuern zoologischen Systeme, nebst dem eigeschalteten Verzeichnisse der zoologischen Sammlungen des Verfassers und den Beschreibungen neuer Thierarten, die in derselben vorhanden sind. Dieterich, Gottingen, XX + 476 pp." type="book" year="1807">
Gravenhorst, 
<number box="[398,454,845,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1807.0">1807</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, C. Giusto des. 
<number box="[644,697,845,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="2015.0">2015</number>
/ 
<taxonomicName authority="Marsham, 1802" authorityName="Marsham" authorityYear="1802" box="[729,1182,845,868]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Perapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hydrolapathi">
<emphasis box="[729,977,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Perapion hydrolapathi</emphasis>
(Marsham, 
<number box="[1117,1174,845,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1802.0">1802</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, det. C. Giusto, 
<number box="[1376,1433,845,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="2015.0">2015</number>
. Measurements: body length: 
<quantity box="[465,564,880,903]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.80 mm</quantity>
, Lr: 
<quantity box="[616,715,880,903]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" unit="mm" value="0.51">0.51 mm</quantity>
, Wmsr: 
<quantity box="[807,906,880,903]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" unit="mm" value="0.21">0.21 mm</quantity>
, Lp: 
<quantity box="[964,1062,880,903]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" unit="mm" value="0.56">0.56 mm</quantity>
, Wp: 
<quantity box="[1128,1227,880,903]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8999999999999995" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" unit="mm" value="0.59">0.59 mm</quantity>
, Le: 
<quantity box="[1283,1381,880,903]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.99" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" unit="mm" value="1.99">1.99 mm</quantity>
, We: 
<quantity box="[151,249,914,937]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" unit="mm" value="1.15">1.15 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,498,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
The following new synonymy is proposed: 
<taxonomicName authority="Marsham, 1802" authorityName="Marsham" authorityYear="1802" box="[667,1104,949,972]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Perapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hydrolapathi">
<emphasis box="[667,911,949,972]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Perapion hydrolapathi</emphasis>
(Marsham, 
<number box="[1042,1097,949,972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1802.0">1802</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName authority="Gravenhorst, 1807" authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1807" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratum" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis box="[1134,1289,949,972]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Apion atratum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gravenhorst" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" refString="Gravenhorst, I. L. C. (1807) Vergleichende Uebersicht des Linneischen und einiger neuern zoologischen Systeme, nebst dem eigeschalteten Verzeichnisse der zoologischen Sammlungen des Verfassers und den Beschreibungen neuer Thierarten, die in derselben vorhanden sind. Dieterich, Gottingen, XX + 476 pp." type="book" year="1807">
Gravenhorst, 
<number box="[151,207,984,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1807.0">1807</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[217,291,984,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[217,291,984,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">syn. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,498,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">
Since 
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner" box="[268,432,1018,1041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" refString="Wagner, H. (1908) 7. Coleoptera. 9. Apioninae. In: Sjostedt, Y. (Ed.), Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der schwedischen zoologischen Expedition nach dem Kilimandjaro, dem Meru und den umgebenden Massaisteppen Deutsch- Ostafrikas 1905 - 1906. 1 Band. Abteilung 1 - 7. Palmquist Aktiebolag, Stockholm, pp. 95 - 104." type="journal article" year="1908">
Wagner (
<number box="[368,423,1018,1041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1908.0">1908</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described another 
<taxonomicName box="[643,801,1018,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratum">
<emphasis box="[643,801,1018,1041]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Apion atratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[873,972,1018,1041]" name="Tanzania" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, currently placed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagner, 1907" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Pseudopiezotrachelus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1202,1436,1018,1041]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Pseudopiezotrachelus</emphasis>
Wagner, 
<number box="[250,306,1053,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1907.0">1907</number>
</taxonomicName>
, the new replacement name 
<taxonomicName box="[632,1014,1053,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Pseudopiezotrachelus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravenhorsti">
<emphasis box="[632,1014,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Pseudopiezotrachelus gravenhorsti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1026,1115,1053,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">nom. n.</emphasis>
, is here proposed for 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagner, 1908" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">Apion atratum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner" box="[243,392,1088,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" refString="Wagner, H. (1908) 7. Coleoptera. 9. Apioninae. In: Sjostedt, Y. (Ed.), Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der schwedischen zoologischen Expedition nach dem Kilimandjaro, dem Meru und den umgebenden Massaisteppen Deutsch- Ostafrikas 1905 - 1906. 1 Band. Abteilung 1 - 7. Palmquist Aktiebolag, Stockholm, pp. 95 - 104." type="journal article" year="1908">
Wagner, 
<number box="[339,392,1088,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1908.0">1908</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(non 
<bibRefCitation author="Gravenhorst" box="[456,659,1088,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" refString="Gravenhorst, I. L. C. (1807) Vergleichende Uebersicht des Linneischen und einiger neuern zoologischen Systeme, nebst dem eigeschalteten Verzeichnisse der zoologischen Sammlungen des Verfassers und den Beschreibungen neuer Thierarten, die in derselben vorhanden sind. Dieterich, Gottingen, XX + 476 pp." type="book" year="1807">
Gravenhorst, 
<number box="[602,659,1088,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1807.0">1807</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The new name is dedicated to the 
<collectingCountry box="[1049,1135,1088,1111]" name="Germany" pageId="1" pageNumber="598">German</collectingCountry>
entomologist, herpetologist and zoologist Johann Ludwig Christian Carl Gravenhorst (Braunschweig, 
<date box="[963,1180,1122,1145]" pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1777-11-14">November 14, 1777</date>
– Breslau, 
<date pageId="1" pageNumber="598" value="1857-01-14">January 14, 1857</date>
).
</paragraph>
